Sentencas: Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (BSCN), originated from SrCo0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (SCN), is investigated as a cathode material in a protonic solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC-H+) with a BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3 (BZCY) electrolyte.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The surface-exchange and bulk-diffusion properties, phase reaction with the electrolyte, electrochemical activity for oxygen reduction, and performance in the real fuel cell condition of SCN and BSCN electrodes are comparatively studied by conductivity relaxation, XRD, EIS and I-V polarization characterizations.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Much better performance is found for BSCN than SCN.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, water has a positive effect on oxygen reduction over BSCN while it has the opposite effect with SCN.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A peak power density of 630 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C is achieved for a thin-film BZCY electrolyte cell with a BSCN cathode compared to only 287 mW cm(-2) for a similar cell with an SCN cathode.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results highly recommend BSCN as a potential cathode material for protonic SOFCs.
Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells

Titulo: A novel Ba0.6Sr0.4Co0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode for protonic solid-oxide fuel cells
